gobblin.state

Class ConstructState

  • java.lang.Object
    • gobblin.configuration.State
      • gobblin.state.ConstructState
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    WritableShim

    public class ConstructState
extends State
    Contains the state of a Gobblin construct at the end of a task. It can be merged with the WorkUnitState, allowing constructs to mutate the WorkUnitState (for example for a changed effective watermark), or add values to report as metadata of task success/failure events.

      • addConstructState

        public void addConstructState(Constructs construct,
                              ConstructState constructState,
                              Optional<String> infix)
        Merge a ConstructState for a child construct into this ConstructState.

        Non-override property names will be mutated as follows: key -> construct.name() + infix + key

        Parameters:
        construct - type of the child construct.
        constructState - ConstructState to merge.
        infix - infix added to each non-override key (for example converter number if there are multiple converters).

      • mergeIntoWorkUnitState

        public void mergeIntoWorkUnitState(WorkUnitState state)
        Merge this ConstructState into a WorkUnitState. All override properties will be added as-is to the , and possibly override already present properties. All other properties have their keys mutated key -> FINAL_CONSTRUCT_STATE_PREFIX + key, and added to the WorkUnitState.
